description: This chicken salad is a lunchtime delight! Packed with creamy avocado, tender chicken, and crunchy veggies, it's a healthy and satisfying meal that won't weigh you down. Tossed in a tangy yogurt dressing with a hint of spice, it's a flavor explosion that's perfect for a light meal.

description: Get ready for a dessert extravaganza with this cinnamon roll cheesecake! Creamy cheesecake filling is baked atop a cinnamon roll crust with a swirl of cinnamon sugar and a final icing glaze for an extra-sweet touch. With all the flavors of a classic cinnamon roll in a decadent cheesecake form, it's a showstopper that'll have everyone asking for seconds!

description: These macarons are a sweet and delicate treat that are perfect for anyone with a nut allergy. Made with a crispy shell and a creamy filling, they're a perfect afternoon snack or dessert.
instructions: [{'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'In a bowl, beat egg whites until frothy.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 14, 'id': 23, 'match': 'beat', 'start_index': 11}], 'id': 52683, 'position': 1, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Gradually add the granulated sugar until stiff peaks form.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 52684, 'position': 2, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'In a separate bowl, whisk the flour and powdered sugar together. description: Dive into layers of savory goodness with this classic comfort food! Tender pasta sheets are layered with a hearty meat sauce, rich cheese, and aromatic herbs and spices, all baked to perfection until bubbly and golden. It's a dish that's perfect for sharing with family and friends, and guaranteed to satisfy your cravings!
instructions: [{'appliance': 'oven', 'display_text': 'Preheat the oven to 375˚F (190˚C).', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 45050, 'position': 1, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': 375}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'In a large bowl, mix together the ricotta, 2 cups (200 G) of mozzarella, 1 cup (110 G) of Parmesan, eggs, parsley and 1 teaspoon salt. Set aside.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 45051, 'position': 2, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'In a large pan, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add the onion and sauté for 2-3 minutes, until translucent. Add the ground beef, breaking up with a wooden spoon. Stir in the garlic, Savory spice blend, and remaining 1½ teaspoons salt. Cook for 8 minutes, until the meat is no longer pink. Add 5 cups (1.3 Kilograms) of marinara sauce and stir to combine.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 45052, 'position': 3, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'To assemble the lasagna, grease a 9 x 13-inch (22 x 33 cm)  baking dish with nonstick spray. Spread the remaining cup of marinara sauce over the bottom of the dish. Lay 4 sheets of lasagna on top of the sauce. Spread 1½ cups (375 G) of the ricotta mixture on top of the noodles. Pour 1½ cups (395 G) of meat sauce on top of the cheese. Repeat with the remaining ingredients, finishing with a layer of meat sauce. Loosely cover the baking dish with foil.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 45053, 'position': 4, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Bake for 40 minutes.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 45054, 'position': 5, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Increase the oven temperature to 500ºF (260˚C). Uncover the lasagna and sprinkle the remaining 1½ cups (150 G) mozzarella and ½ cup (55 G) Parmesan over the top.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 45055, 'position': 6, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Bake the lasagna for 5 minutes more, until the cheese is bubbly and browned.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 74, 'id': 13, 'match': 'browned', 'start_index': 68}], 'id': 45056, 'position': 7, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Enjoy!', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 45057, 'position': 8, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}]

description: You won't believe your eyes when you see this 100-layer lasagna! It's a tower of deliciousness filled with layers of pasta, meat sauce, ricotta cheese, and mozzarella cheese. It's like a work of art that you can eat!
instructions: [{'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Lay down about 6 feet (1.8 meters) of tinfoil on a flat surface. Place place 4 clusters of 2 lasagna noodles towards the left half of the foil sheet, leaving about a ½-inch (1 cm) gap in between each cluster.', 'end_time': 12883, 'id': 32688, 'position': 1, 'start_time': 2833, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Fold the right half of foil over the noodles, pressing flat. To help you see where the noodles are, run your finger along the edges of the noodles to create a rough outline in the foil.', 'end_time': 19383, 'id': 32689, 'position': 2, 'start_time': 12883, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Fold the top and bottom flaps of foil over, creasing and pressing flat.', 'end_time': 20716, 'id': 32690, 'position': 3, 'start_time': 19550, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Flip the foil sheet onto the table so that it’s now standing, then arrange into a square box, using the 4 groups of noodles as a visual guide. Fold and crease over any excess foil to join the ends together, then set aside.', 'end_time': 23216, 'id': 32691, 'position': 4, 'start_time': 20716, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'In a large pot, melt the butter over medium heat.', 'end_time': 27049, 'id': 32692, 'position': 5, 'start_time': 24216, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Whisk in the flour, cooking until the mixture reaches a light golden color.', 'end_time': 32766, 'id': 32693, 'position': 6, 'start_time': 27216, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Slowly drizzle in the milk and bring to a boil, whisking constantly until smooth. Mix in salt, pepper, and nutmeg. Bring to a boil.', 'end_time': 45766, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 45, 'id': 18, 'match': 'boil', 'start_index': 42}, {'end_index': 55, 'id': 24, 'match': 'whisking', 'start_index': 48}], 'id': 32694, 'position': 7, 'start_time': 32933, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Transfer the béchamel to a large bowl and press plastic wrap onto the surface of the sauce to prevent a skin from forming. Set aside.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 32695, 'position': 8, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Heat oil in a very large pot over high heat. Once the oil begins to shimmer, add the onions, carrots, and celery and cook until the vegetables have started to sweat but aren’t browning.', 'end_time': 52983, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 183, 'id': 13, 'match': 'browning', 'start_index': 176}], 'id': 32696, 'position': 9, 'start_time': 46766, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Add in the ground beef and use a wooden spoon or spatula to break up the meat into small pieces.', 'end_time': 55666, 'id': 32697, 'position': 10, 'start_time': 53150, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Cook the beef, stirring occasionally, until half of the liquid has evaporated.', 'end_time': 58333, 'id': 32698, 'position': 11, 'start_time': 55666, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Add in the tomato sauce, tomato paste, chicken stock, salt, and pepper, stirring to combine evenly and breaking up any last lumps.', 'end_time': 73716, 'id': 32699, 'position': 12, 'start_time': 58500, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Turn down the heat to low, and simmer, covered, for about 2 hours.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 36, 'id': 17, 'match': 'simmer', 'start_index': 31}], 'id': 32700, 'position': 13, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': 'oven', 'display_text': 'Preheat oven to 350°F (180°C).', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 32687, 'position': 14, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': 350}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'To assemble, line a greased 9x9-inch (23x23-cm) square baking pan with 2 sheets of foil that extend over the sides.', 'end_time': 87100, 'id': 32701, 'position': 15, 'start_time': 82550, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Spread a thin layer of béchamel on the lined baking pan and top with 2 lasagna noodles. Spread a thin layer of meat sauce evenly across the noodles, followed by a thin layer of béchamel. Repeat the layering process, following the order of: 2 noodles, meat sauce, and béchamel. Alternate the direction of the lasagna sheets after every layer.', 'end_time': 110483, 'id': 32702, 'position': 16, 'start_time': 87266, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'After 50 layers, place the foil box over the lasagna, helping it stay upright and stable.', 'end_time': 117816, 'id': 32703, 'position': 17, 'start_time': 110650, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Continue with the layering process until the 99th layer.', 'end_time': 136366, 'id': 32704, 'position': 18, 'start_time': 117983, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Sprinkle Parmesan on top, then cover the whole lasagna with foil.', 'end_time': 148700, 'id': 32705, 'position': 19, 'start_time': 136366, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Bake for about 1½ hours, uncovering the foil halfway, until the top is a deep golden brown.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 32706, 'position': 20, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Cool for at least 2 hours, then carefully lift out the lasagna with the foil sleeves onto a large cutting board.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 32707, 'position': 21, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Peel away the foil walls, then sprinkle the top of the lasagna generously with chives.', 'end_time': 162416, 'id': 32708, 'position': 22, 'start_time': 154700, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Cut and serve.', 'end_time': 186966, 'id': 32709, 'position': 23, 'start_time': 163916, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Enjoy!', 'end_time': 195683, 'id': 32721, 'position': 24, 'start_time': 188466, 'temperature': None}]

description: Say hello to a taste of the bayou with this creamy Cajun pasta! Savory sausage and a bevy of vegetables get a spicy kick with a Cajun-inspired seasoning blend, all tossed in a luscious creamy sauce. Best of all, it all comes together in just one pot for easy prep and clean-up!
instructions: [{'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'In a large, heavy-bottomed pot, melt the butter over medium heat until just bubbling. Add the sausage, then season with salt. Brown for 2 minutes on one side, then stir and brown on the other side for 2 minutes more.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44910, 'position': 1, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Add the onion, season with salt, and cook for 2 minutes, until starting to soften. Add the jalapeño, garlic, and tomato paste. Stir to distribute the tomato paste. Add the Jazzy spice blend and stir to combine.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44911, 'position': 2, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Add the pasta, red and green peppers, mushrooms, and salt and stir to combine. Pour in the tomatoes and stock. Bring to a gentle boil, then reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 10-12 minutes, until the pasta is cooked through and the peppers are tender but not mushy.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 180, 'id': 17, 'match': 'simmer', 'start_index': 175}, {'end_index': 132, 'id': 18, 'match': 'boil', 'start_index': 129}, {'end_index': 233, 'id': 21, 'match': 'cooked through', 'start_index': 220}], 'id': 44912, 'position': 3, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Mix in the cream cheese to create a thick, creamy sauce.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44913, 'position': 4, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Serve garnished with scallions, if desired.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44914, 'position': 5, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Enjoy!', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44915, 'position': 6, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}]

description: Al pastor’s signature red-hued marinade produces flavorful bites of whatever it coats. Traditionally used to marinate meat, you can also enjoy the same punch of flavor with a vegan alternative. Here, we use butternut squash for its hearty texture and subtle sweetness, which play well with the warm al pastor spices.
instructions: [{'appliance': 'oven', 'display_text': 'Preheat the oven to 350°F (180°C). Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 53389, 'position': 1, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': 350}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'In a large bowl, toss the butternut squash with the achiote powder, ancho chile powder, garlic powder, onion powder, coriander, thyme, cumin, salt, black pepper, cayenne, apple cider vinegar, orange juice, and 2 tablespoons of olive oil until well coated. Spread the butternut squash in an even layer on a prepared baking sheet.', 'end_time': 36000, 'id': 53390, 'position': 2, 'start_time': 7999, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Bake the squash for 45 minutes, tossing halfway, until deepened in color and the spices have darkened.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 53391, 'position': 3, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Add the pineapple to the same bowl where the butternut squash was seasoned and toss to coat in the remaining marinade. Spread in an even layer on the remaining prepared baking sheet.', 'end_time': 62000, 'id': 53392, 'position': 4, 'start_time': 48333, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Bake the pineapple for 25–30 minutes, until softened and slightly shrunken.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 53393, 'position': 5, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Toss the roasted butternut squash with the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil on the baking sheet.', 'end_time': 75833, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 15, 'id': 14, 'match': 'roasted', 'start_index': 9}], 'id': 53394, 'position': 6, 'start_time': 66000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Warm the tortillas, one at a time, directly over a medium flame on a stovetop burner until the edges are charred and the tortillas are pliable. Keep warm by wrapping in a kitchen towel while you repeat with the remaining tortillas. Alternatively, microwave the tortillas until warmed through.', 'end_time': 86833, 'id': 53395, 'position': 7, 'start_time': 80000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'To assemble the tacos, spoon butternut squash and pineapple into each tortilla. Top with onion, cilantro, and avocado. Serve with lime wedges.', 'end_time': 107333, 'id': 53396, 'position': 8, 'start_time': 90000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Enjoy!', 'end_time': 112833, 'id': 53397, 'position': 9, 'start_time': 109000, 'temperature': None}]

description: Satisfy your cravings with this savory spaghetti and meatball dish that's bursting with flavor. This classic comfort food, inspired by Tasty.co and Rachel Ray, will have your taste buds dancing and your family asking for seconds.
instructions: [{'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Make the sauce: In a large pot over medium-low heat, combine the olive oil and garlic and cook until the garlic begins to sizzle very gently. Add the red pepper flakes and cook, stirring, until the garlic just begins to turn light golden in color, about 3 minutes. Add the Savory spice blend and continue to cook, stirring, for 1 minute more.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 45058, 'position': 1, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Add the tomato paste and cook, stirring, until the paste has softened and blended with the oil and garlic mixture, about 3 minutes.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 45059, 'position': 2, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Stir in the tomatoes and their juices and increase the heat to medium-high, bringing the to a gentle simmer. Lower the heat a bit if it’s bubbling and spitting too much. Remove the sauce from the heat.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 106, 'id': 17, 'match': 'simmer', 'start_index': 101}], 'id': 45060, 'position': 3, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Using an immersion blender, blend the sauce until smooth. Tip: Drape a kitchen towel over the pot to act as a cover from sauce splatters. Or, transfer the sauce to a blender and puree, then return to the pot.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 45061, 'position': 4, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Decrease the heat to medium-low and bring the sauce to a simmer.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [], 'id': 45062, 'position': 5, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Make the meatballs: In a medium bowl, combine the bread cubes, cream, parmesan, onion, garlic, and pepper. Using a fork, mash into thick paste.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 45063, 'position': 6, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'In a large bowl, gently mix the ground pork with the salt and baking powder. Add the beef and gently stir to combine (you can also use your hands for this). Add the bread mixture, Savory spice blend, and a pinch more salt and pepper and mix until just incorporated. Rub a bit of olive oil on your hands and form the mixture into smooth, round meatballs the size of golf balls--you should have about 25 total..', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 45064, 'position': 7, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Once the meatballs are formed, gently lower each meatball into the pot of sauce. Bring to a low simmer, cover, and cook for 25-35 minutes, or until a meat thermometer inserted into a meatball reaches 165˚F (75˚C).', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [], 'id': 45065, 'position': 8, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'While the meatballs are cooking, bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Cook the spaghetti according to the package instructions. Reserve 1 cup (240 ml) of pasta cooking water, then drain.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 75, 'id': 18, 'match': 'boil', 'start_index': 72}], 'id': 45066, 'position': 9, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'In a large bowl, toss the spaghetti with a few large spoonfuls of pasta sauce to coat, along with a few splashes of the reserved cooking water. Divide the pasta among bowls and spoon more sauce and meatballs over the pasta. Top each serving with freshly grated Parmesan and basil.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 45067, 'position': 10, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Enjoy!', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 45068, 'position': 11, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}]

description: This seacuterie board is sure to make a splash at your next dinner party. From shrimp and seaweed salad to octopus and oranges, have fun with your favorite seafood and side bites. Then present them on a sheet pan for easy serving. Plus, learn how to shuck your own oysters.
instructions: [{'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'The day before serving, make the octopus salad: In a large bowl, whisk together the orange zest, orange juice, ginger juice, garlic, soy sauce, sesame oil, mirin, apple cider vinegar, jalapeño, sugar, olive oil, and salt. Add the octopus and toss to coat. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and marinate the octopus in the refrigerator overnight.', 'end_time': 39500, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 69, 'id': 24, 'match': 'whisk', 'start_index': 65}], 'id': 54639, 'position': 1, 'start_time': 7000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Make the mignonette sauce: In a small serving bowl, stir together the shallot, red wine vinegar, and crushed black peppercorns. Refrigerate until ready to serve.', 'end_time': 51500, 'id': 54640, 'position': 2, 'start_time': 43000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Make the crab dip. In a medium bowl, stir together the cream cheese, mayonnaise, Old Bay seasoning, garlic powder, horseradish, lemon zest and juice, Worcestershire sauce, and salt. Mix well. Gently fold in the crab meat and chives, then season with the salt. Refrigerate until ready to serve.', 'end_time': 82000, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 205, 'id': 22, 'match': 'fold in', 'start_index': 199}], 'id': 54641, 'position': 3, 'start_time': 52000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Shuck the oysters: Wrap a kitchen towel around your hand and an oyster, leaving the pointed end of the oyster exposed. Using an oyster knife, carefully wedge the knife into one side of the point and use firm, even pressure to twist to open the oyster. Unwrap the oyster from the towel, then use the knife to work around the top shell, disconnecting the muscle. Remove the top shell and gently run the knife along the bottom shell to release the oyster. Repeat with the remaining oysters. Arrange the oysters in the bottom shells on a small platter of crushed ice with the mignonette sauce and a lemon half.', 'end_time': 111333, 'id': 54642, 'position': 4, 'start_time': 85000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Assemble the board: Spread the crushed ice on a 26 x 18-inch baking sheet. Top with the other baking sheet. Line with butcher’s paper.', 'end_time': 125333, 'id': 54643, 'position': 5, 'start_time': 114000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Transfer the octopus salad to a serving dish and garnish with the micro cilantro, then place on the pan, along with the oyster platter. Transfer the crab dip to a serving dish and place on the pan, then garnish with chives. Add the butter lettuce leaves, then top with the ahi poke salad. Arrange the lox, cocktail shrimp, cocktail sauce, prepared horseradish, seaweed salad, grilled bread, crackers, cucumber, crab claws, blood orange slices, and pickled vegetables. Top the lox with the capers. Add the lemons to the pan.', 'end_time': 196000, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 440, 'id': 6, 'match': 'slice', 'start_index': 436}, {'end_index': 382, 'id': 16, 'match': 'grilled', 'start_index': 376}], 'id': 54644, 'position': 6, 'start_time': 126000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Serve immediately.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 54645, 'position': 7, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Enjoy!', 'end_time': 218166, 'id': 54646, 'position': 8, 'start_time': 209000, 'temperature': None}]

description: Get ready for a protein-packed delight with this Mediterranean-inspired dish! Crispy quinoa rice cakes topped with tender and juicy Mediterranean-spiced chicken, tomatoes, and briny kalamata olives. It's a wholesome and satisfying meal that's perfect for a healthy and delicious dinner.
instructions: [{'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Mix together the garlic, salt, pepper, olive oil, and lemon juice to form a marinade.', 'end_time': 334000, 'id': 44581, 'position': 1, 'start_time': 326000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Toss the chicken in the mixture and let marinate for 15–20 minutes.', 'end_time': 341000, 'id': 44583, 'position': 2, 'start_time': 334000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Cut open the packages of Seeds of Change Organic Quinoa and Brown Rice with Garlic so that the opening is approximately 2 inches (5 cm) wide.', 'end_time': 382622, 'id': 44584, 'position': 3, 'start_time': 341001, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Microwave packages for 90 seconds, then place contents into a bowl.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44586, 'position': 4, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Add the rest of the rice cake ingredients, except the olive oil, and mix well.', 'end_time': 381000, 'id': 44587, 'position': 5, 'start_time': 344000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Remove approximately ⅓ of the mixture and pulse it well in a food processor.', 'end_time': 372000, 'id': 44589, 'position': 6, 'start_time': 370000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Add the pulsed quinoa back into the rest of the mixture and combine well.', 'end_time': 380000, 'id': 44591, 'position': 7, 'start_time': 373000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'To shape quinoa cakes, take about ⅓ cup (45 g) of quinoa mixture and, using your hands, shape into a small patty. Repeat with the rest of the quinoa mixture.', 'end_time': 389000, 'id': 44592, 'position': 8, 'start_time': 382000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Heat the olive oil in a large skillet. Cook the quinoa cakes for 3–4 minutes on each side until golden brown. Remove from skillet.', 'end_time': 389000, 'id': 44595, 'position': 9, 'start_time': 384000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Heat a drizzle of olive oil in another skillet. Sear marinated chicken on both sides.', 'end_time': 394000, 'id': 44597, 'position': 10, 'start_time': 382000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': 'oven', 'display_text': 'Cover pan with a lid to continue cooking chicken until internal temperature reaches 165ºF (75ºFC).', 'end_time': 395000, 'id': 44599, 'position': 11, 'start_time': 392000, 'temperature': 165}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Move chicken to a cutting board and let rest for 5 minutes.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44601, 'position': 12, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Slice chicken into thin slices.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 28, 'id': 6, 'match': 'slice', 'start_index': 24}], 'id': 44602, 'position': 13, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'To assemble, place a couple pieces of chicken on a quinoa cake.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44603, 'position': 14, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Garnish with tomatoes, then place a second quinoa cake on top to form a sandwich.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44604, 'position': 15, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Enjoy!', 'end_time': 436622, 'id': 44605, 'position': 16, 'start_time': 395001, 'temperature': None}]

If the grits are bubbling and spurting too much, cover the pot partially with a lid, but make sure not to cover fully. Continue whisking frequently until the grits are tender, about 1 hour. Whether you're serving it up for a backyard barbecue or a cozy dinner at home, this fried chicken will have you tapping your toes and craving seconds in no time. So, grab your apron and get ready to fry up some finger-lickin' goodness that'll have everyone singing your praises!

description: Rich and creamy potatoes au gratin with extra depth of flavor from tons of roasted garlic. This is the perfect dish to amp up an Easter spread or pair with a roast that creates minimal dirty dishes!
instructions: [{'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C). Grease an 8x8-inch square baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 76322, 'position': 1, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Use a sharp knife to cut off the tops of the garlic heads and place them cut-side up on a large piece of foil. Drizzle the exposed garlic cloves with olive oil and season with salt. Bring up the corners of the foil around the garlic, then roll closed to form a tight packet. Place the packet on a baking sheet and roast in the preheated oven for about 45 minutes, or until the garlic is caramelized. Remove from the oven and let sit for about 15 minutes, or until cool enough to handle.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 318, 'id': 14, 'match': 'roast', 'start_index': 314}], 'id': 76323, 'position': 2, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Unwrap the foil packet and squeeze the heads to release the roasted garlic cloves into an upright blender. Blend until the sauce is smooth.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [], 'id': 76324, 'position': 3, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Arrange the sliced potatoes in even rows in the prepared baking dish.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 17, 'id': 6, 'match': 'sliced', 'start_index': 12}], 'id': 76325, 'position': 4, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Pour the sauce over the potatoes, making sure to get in between the potato slices.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [], 'id': 76326, 'position': 5, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Evenly top the potatoes with the remaining ½ cup Gruyère, ½ cup cheddar, and 2 tablespoons Parmesan. description: Vegan caesar has never been easier thanks to this time saving hack! Using hummus as the base of the dressing gives you richness while being both nut and dairy free. Adjust the consistency to your liking by adding more hummus for a thicker dressing or more water for thinner. This dressing is packed with flavor thanks to brininess from the capers, cheesiness from the nutritional yeast, and umami from the miso.

description: This dish is a flavorful and easy way to create a hearty and delicious meal all in one pot! Tender chicken thighs are baked to juicy perfection with a medley of colorful veggies and seasoned with zesty lemon and basil. It's a perfect combination of flavors and textures that will leave your taste buds dancing and your family satisfied.
instructions: [{'appliance': 'oven', 'display_text': 'Preheat the oven to 375˚F (190˚C).', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44900, 'position': 1, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': 375}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'In a small bowl, combine 1 tablespoon of the Zesty spice blend, 1 teaspoon salt, and the pepper. Transfer the chicken to a plate and set aside.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44902, 'position': 3, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Reduce the heat to medium. Bake for 35 minutes, until the rice is cooked through, but not mushy, and the chicken temperature reaches 165˚F (75˚C).', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 99, 'id': 21, 'match': 'cooked through', 'start_index': 86}], 'id': 44906, 'position': 7, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Remove the chicken from the pot. Squeeze the juice from a lemon half into the rice and fluff with a fork, allowing some steam to escape and halt additional cooking.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44907, 'position': 8, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Transfer the rice and chicken to plates and top with fresh basil. Cut the remaining lemon half into wedges and serve on the side.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44908, 'position': 9, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Enjoy!', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44909, 'position': 10, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}]

description: This dish is a delicious and hearty way to enjoy the rich and tender flavors of lamb chops! The chops are seasoned with a blend of aromatic spices, marinated and seared to  juicy perfection, then served on a bed of fluffy and flavorful couscous. It's a perfect combination of textures and flavors that will leave your taste buds satisfied and your stomach full.

instructions: [{'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Make the chocolate finger sandwiches: Remove the Breyers® Chocolate Ice Cream from the freezer and let soften at room temperature for 5 minutes.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 59171, 'position': 1, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Line a loaf pan with plastic wrap. Scoop the chocolate ice cream into the pan. Using an offset spatula, spread the ice cream in an even layer, making sure it goes all the way to the corners. Freeze for 2 hours, or until solid.', 'end_time': 41500, 'id': 59172, 'position': 2, 'start_time': 35000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 59173, 'position': 3, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Turn the pound cake on its side and use a serrated knife to slice about ½ inch off the top and bottom of the cake. You should be left with a large, flat rectangle of cake, about 1 inch thick. Slice the rectangle in half so you have 2 flat rectangles about ½ inch thick. Transfer to the prepared baking sheet. Discard the scraps or save for another use.', 'end_time': 58166, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 64, 'id': 6, 'match': 'slice', 'start_index': 60}], 'id': 59174, 'position': 4, 'start_time': 43000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Remove the loaf pan with the chocolate ice cream from the freezer and use the plastic wrap to lift the ice cream from the pan. Place the ice cream facedown on a pound cake rectangle, then peel off the plastic and place the other cake rectangle on top.', 'end_time': 60833, 'id': 59175, 'position': 5, 'start_time': 59000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Using a sharp knife (wipe clean after each cut), trim ¼ inch from all sides of the cake to make even edges. Transfer the ice cream cake sandwich to the freezer for 1–2 hours, until solid.', 'end_time': 64833, 'id': 59176, 'position': 6, 'start_time': 63000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Remove the cake sandwich from the freezer and slice crosswise into 8 rectangular finger sandwiches. (If you prefer triangles, cut crosswise into 3 squares, then slice diagonally in half for 6 finger sandwiches.)', 'end_time': 69333, 'hacks': [], 'id': 59177, 'position': 7, 'start_time': 66000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Working quickly, dip the sandwiches in or drizzle with the melted chocolate. Decorate with the sprinkles, then return to the baking sheet and freeze for at least 1 hour, or until ready to serve.', 'end_time': 79500, 'id': 59178, 'position': 8, 'start_time': 70000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Make the edible teacups: Use a serrated knife to carefully cut about ½ inch from the bottom of a cake cone cup. Discard the base.', 'end_time': 6000, 'id': 59179, 'position': 9, 'start_time': 4000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Pipe a line of royal icing around the cut edge of the cone, then gently press onto the center of a shortbread cookie to make the teacup base. Cut a coated pretzel ring in half and pipe a dot of icing on to each end. Gently press onto the side of the cone, making the teacup handle.', 'end_time': 18000, 'id': 59180, 'position': 10, 'start_time': 6000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Repeat with the remaining ingredients to make 8 teacups total. Freeze for 30 minutes, or until the icing is set and the teacups hold together.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 59181, 'position': 11, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Add a small scoop of Breyers® Natural Strawberry Ice Cream, Breyers® Natural Vanilla Ice Cream, or Breyers® Mint Chocolate Chip Ice Cream to each teacup, then freeze again until ready to serve. Decorate with natural toppings, if desired.', 'end_time': 85666, 'id': 59182, 'position': 12, 'start_time': 80000, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Enjoy your Breyers® Ice Cream Tea Party!', 'end_time': 87000, 'id': 59183, 'position': 13, 'start_time': 86000, 'temperature': None}]

description: This Buddha bowl is a healthy and delicious way to fuel your body with wholesome ingredients. Packed with protein-rich tofu, nutrient-dense veggies, and fluffy quinoa, this bowl is a colorful feast for both your eyes and taste buds. The creamy peanut dressing adds the perfect finishing touch to this satisfying and nourishing meal.
instructions: [{'appliance': 'oven', 'display_text': 'Preheat the oven to 400˚F (200˚C).', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44835, 'position': 1, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': 400}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Make the tofu marinade: In a medium bowl, mix together the sesame oil, mirin, Fiery spice blend, and salt.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44836, 'position': 2, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Cut the tofu lengthwise into ½-inch (1 ¼ cm) wide slabs, then cut each slab in half lengthwise. Cut each strip into ½-inch (1 ¼ cm) wide cubes. Toss with the marinade, then cover with plastic wrap marinate in the fridge for at least 1 hour.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44837, 'position': 3, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Fill a large pot with cold water, season well with salt, and add the sweet potatoes. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Reduce the heat to low and simmer until the sweet potatoes can be pierced with a fork but still give some resistance, about 20 minutes.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 156, 'id': 17, 'match': 'simmer', 'start_index': 151}, {'end_index': 99, 'id': 18, 'match': 'boil', 'start_index': 96}], 'id': 44838, 'position': 4, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Remove sweet potatoes from the pot and set aside to cool. Drop in the broccoli florets and blanch for 90 seconds. Remove the broccoli and shock in an ice bath to stop the cooking. Cool completely, about 60 seconds, then transfer to a paper towel-lined plate to drain.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 96, 'id': 15, 'match': 'blanch', 'start_index': 91}], 'id': 44839, 'position': 5, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Cut the cooled sweet potato into ½-inch (1 ¼ cm) wide half moons and season with salt to taste.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44840, 'position': 6, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'On a lightly greased baking sheet, spread out the marinated tofu and sweet potato. Bake for 20 minutes, until sweet potatoes and tofu begin to brown.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44841, 'position': 7, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'While the sweet potatoes and tofu cook, make the peanut sauce: In a medium bowl, whisk together the peanut butter, apple cider vinegar, Fiery spice blend, and ¼ cup water. Season with salt to taste.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 85, 'id': 24, 'match': 'whisk', 'start_index': 81}], 'id': 44842, 'position': 8, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Assemble the bowls: Add 1 cup (170 G) of quinoa to the bottom of a serving bowl, then arrange about 2½ ounces (70 G) of tofu, ½ cup (112 G) sweet potato, ½ cup (75 G) broccoli florets, ½ cup (50 G) purple cabbage, ¼ cup (30 G) cucumber, and 4-5 slices of avocado on top. Drizzle with 2-3 tablespoons peanut sauce and top with crushed peanuts, cilantro, and mint.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 249, 'id': 6, 'match': 'slice', 'start_index': 245}], 'id': 44843, 'position': 9, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Enjoy!', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44844, 'position': 10, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}]

description: It's comfort food at its finest with this classic duo–roasted tomato soup and grilled cheese sandwiches! Sweet, tangy tomatoes are roasted to perfection, then blended into a velvety soup that's full of flavor. Paired with gooey, melty grilled cheese sandwiches oozing with cheesy goodness, it's the ultimate combination that'll warm your heart and soul.

description: This dish is a simple yet elegant way to enjoy the delicate flavors of white fish! The fish is cooked to flaky perfection and served with a bed of tangy and sweet simmered tomatoes, creating a perfect balance of flavors. It's a savory and satisfying meal that's easy to prepare and sure to impress.

description: The fiery chicken wings are a deliciously spicy finger food for any party or gathering.
instructions: [{'appliance': 'oven', 'display_text': 'Preheat the oven to 350ºF (180˚C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44936, 'position': 1, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': 350}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Season the wings all over with salt and pepper and set on the prepared baking sheet.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44937, 'position': 2, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Bake the wings until the internal temperature reaches 165ºF (74˚C), about 20 minutes.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44938, 'position': 3, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Heat 1 inch of canola oil in a large pot over medium heat until it reaches 350ºF (180˚C).', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44939, 'position': 4, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'While the oil heats, make the wing sauce. In a medium skillet, gently melt the butter over medium heat. Once melted, add the lime juice, garlic, honey, and Fiery spice blend. Bring to a simmer, whisking to combine. Cook until the sauce comes together and thickens slightly, about 3 minutes.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 191, 'id': 17, 'match': 'simmer', 'start_index': 186}, {'end_index': 201, 'id': 24, 'match': 'whisking', 'start_index': 194}], 'id': 44940, 'position': 5, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Make cornstarch slurry: stir together cornstarch and cold water, breaking up any clumps, you should be left with a milk like consistency. Whisk cornstarch slurry into the sauce, bring up to a low boil, whisking continuously until thickened. Season with salt to taste. Remove the sauce from the heat and set aside.', 'end_time': 0, 'hacks': [{'end_index': 199, 'id': 18, 'match': 'boil', 'start_index': 196}], 'id': 44941, 'position': 6, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Working in batches, carefully lower 4-6 wings at a time into the hot oil. Fry for 2-3 minutes, until the skin is golden brown and crispy. Repeat with the remaining wings.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44942, 'position': 7, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'In a large bowl, toss 4-6 wings at a time with ¼-⅓ cup of the sauce until well coated. Repeat with the remaining wings.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44943, 'position': 8, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Garnish the wings with cilantro, lime zest, and a pinch of Fiery spice blend, if desired. Serve hot.', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44944, 'position': 9, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Nutrition  Calories: 1701 Fat: 135 grams  Carbs: 63 grams Fiber: 2 grams  Sugars: 53 grams  Protein: 69 grams', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 45281, 'position': 10, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}, {'appliance': None, 'display_text': 'Enjoy!', 'end_time': 0, 'id': 44945, 'position': 11, 'start_time': 0, 'temperature': None}]
